  "text": "Kinema is an indigenous food that represents the diverse food culture of the ethnic communities of Nepal. It is a sticky fermented soybean food with a sticky texture, gray-tan in color, and flavorful produced by natural fermentation. Kinema is similar to other Asians Bacillus-fermented sticky soybean foods such as natto of Japan, chungkukjang of Korea, thua nao of northern Thailand, pe-poke of Myanmar, and sieng of Cambodia [CITATION_1] .",
